(32, 'Leo Messi will receive part his pay in cryptocurrency. Should you do the same?', 'Messis deal with Paris Saint-Germain includes a large number of fan tokens for the French football club ', 'Lionel Messi, the soccer player with the famed left foot coming to Paris Saint-Germain, just made quite the play — into cryptocurrency.\r\nAs part of his contract with the renowned French team, Messi is receiving an unspecified large number of PSG fan tokens, according to the club.\r\nThese are a form of cryptocurrency that, among other things, give owners the right to vote on certain aspects of the team.\r\nPSG fan token owners get a say in naming the years best goal, who wins the year-end team award and the motivational message that appears on the dressing room wall.\r\nInternationally-known soccer teams such as Italys AC Milan, and Englands Manchester United, have fan tokens. So does UFC, the mixed martial arts league.\r\nThe fan tokens in Messis welcome package are just one part of the 34-year-old Argentines two-year contract with an option for a third year at Paris Saint-Germain thats reportedly in the range of €25 million to €30 million ($25.3 million to $35.2 million), according to Reuters.\r\nMessis big batch of fan tokens provides a high-profile glimpse of an emerging way of getting paid via cryptocurrency and digital assets — in professional sports and elsewhere.\r\nIn 2020, American football player Russell Okung, an offensive tackle whos a free agent, said he would put half of his $13 million salary into bitcoin BTCUSD, 0.88%.\r\nLast month, New York Giants running back Saquon Barkley said he’ll accept pay for all his future\r\n', 'images (2).jfif', 2, NULL, '2021-08-21 10:34:57'),
(33, 'មនុស្សជាង ៤២៣,០០០ នាក់នៅកម្ពុជាបានចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសជំរុញទី៣ ដើម្បីបង្ការជំងឺ-១៩', 'ក្នុងរយៈពេល ១២ ថ្ងៃចាប់តាំងពីការចាប់ផ្តើមយុទ្ធនាការចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសជំរុញដល់បុគ្គលិកជួរមុខនៅក្នុងខេត្តចំនួន ៧ ដែលប្រឈមនឹងការមកដល់ពលករចំណាកស្រុកយ៉ាងច្រើនដែលប្រញាប់ប្រញាល់ឆ្លងកាត់ ពលករនិងបុគ្គលិកជួរមុខផ្សេងទៀតសរុបចំនួន ៤២៣,៩៤៧ ប', 'ក្នុងរយៈពេល ១២ ថ្ងៃចាប់តាំងពីការចាប់ផ្តើមយុទ្ធនាការចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសជំរុញដល់បុគ្គលិកជួរមុខនៅក្នុងខេត្តចំនួន ៧ ដែលប្រឈមនឹងការមកដល់ពលករចំណាកស្រុកយ៉ាងច្រើនដែលប្រញាប់ប្រញាល់ឆ្លងកាត់ ពលករនិងបុគ្គលិកជួរមុខផ្សេងទៀតសរុបចំនួន ៤២៣,៩៤៧ បានចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំង AstraZeneca ដើម្បីបង្ការក្រុមមនុស្សដែលមានហានិភ័យខ្ពស់។\r\nយុទ្ធនាការចាក់ដូសជំរុញដែលប្រើតែវ៉ាក់សាំងប្រភេទ AstraZeneca ដែលកម្ពុជាមានជិត ១.៥ លានដូសដោយទទួលបានពីប្រទេសជប៉ុន ១ លានដូស និងចក្រភពអង់គ្លេសចំនួន ៤១៥,០០០ ដូស បានចាប់ផ្តើមនៅថ្ងៃទី ៨ ខែសីហា នៅក្នុងខេត្តចំនួន ៧ ដែលកំពុងមានពលករចំណាកស្រុកមកពីប្រទេសថៃយ៉ាងច្រើនជារៀងរាល់ថ្ងៃ ចាប់តាំងពីព្រំដែនបានបើកទ្វារឡើងវិញនៅថ្ងៃទី ១៣ ខែសីហា បន្ទាប់ពីបិទខ្ទប់អស់រយៈពេលពីរសប្តាហ៍។\r\nក្នុងចំណោមចំនួនសរុប ៤២៣,៩៤៧ នាក់ មានស្រី្តចំនួន ១៤១,៤៦៤ នាក់ ហើយនៅថ្ងៃខាងមុខ ការចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសជំរុញនេះត្រូវបានគេរំពឹងថានឹងសម្រេចបានយ៉ាងពេញលេញនៅក្នុងខេត្តដែលបានកំណត់ មុនពេលយុទ្ធនាការផ្លាស់ទៅធ្វើនៅតំបន់ដែលមានហានិភ័យខ្ពស់ផ្សេងទៀត ដូចជាខេត្តដែលមានចំនួនករណីឆ្លងជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ខ្ពស់ និងការកើនឡើងការឆ្លងវីរុសប្រភេទ Delta។\r\nក្រសួងសុខាភិបាលបានបញ្ជាក់រួចហើយថា មិនទាន់មានការសម្រេចចិត្តនៅឡើយទេថាតើអ្នកដែលបានទទួលវ៉ាក់សាំងប្រភេទស៊ីណូហ្វាម ឬស៊ីណូវ៉ាក់ទាំងអស់នឹងចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសជំរុញទី៣ឬទេ ដូចគ្នាដែរ អ្នកដែលបានចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំង AstraZeneca ពីរដងហើយថាតើពួកគេនឹងត្រូវចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងណាមួយរបស់ចិនជាដូសជំរុញដែររឺអត់។\r\nសហរដ្ឋអាមេរិកដែលជាប្រទេសដំបូងគេនៅលើពិភពលោកដែលចាប់ផ្តើមចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងបង្ការជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ ទើបតែសម្រេចចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងបង្ការដូសជំរុញជាផ្លូវការនៅដើមសប្តាហ៍នេះ ខណៈវ៉ាក់សាំង PfizerBiontech និង Moderna របស់ខ្លួន ដែលជាវ៉ាក់សាំងត្រូវប្រើជាចម្បងនៅសហរដ្ឋអាមេរិកបង្ហាញពីការបាត់បង់ប្រសិទ្ធភាពយ៉ាងខ្លាំង ក្រោយពីចាក់រួចរយៈពេល ៦ ខែ។\r\nការចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំង Pfizer និង Moderna ដូសជំរុញបង្ការជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ ត្រូវបានកំណត់ចាក់ឱ្យគ្រប់ពលរដ្ឋអាមេរិកពេញវ័យទាំងអស់ ដោយចាប់ផ្តើមនៅខែក្រោយ។\r\nវេជ្ជបណ្ឌិត Vivek Murthy គ្រូពេទ្យវះកាត់ទូទៅបាននិយាយនៅឯសន្និសីទកាសែតនៅសេតវិមានថា “យើងដឹងថាសូម្បីវ៉ាក់សាំងដែលមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពខ្ពស់ ក៏បាត់បង់មិនសូវមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពតាមពេលវេលាដែរ។ បច្ចុប្បន្ននេះ វាគឺជាការវិនិច្ឆ័យរបស់យើងដែលថាពេលវេលារៀបចំផែនការសម្រាប់ចាក់ដូសជំរុញកូវីដគឺដល់ពេលហើយ។\r\nវេជ្ជបណ្ឌិត Vivek Murthy គ្រូពេទ្យវះកាត់ទូទៅបាននិយាយនៅឯសន្និសីទកាសែតនៅសេតវិមានថា យើងដឹងថាសូម្បីវ៉ាក់សាំងដែលមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពខ្ពស់ ក៏បាត់បង់មិនសូវមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពតាមពេលវេលាដែរ។ បច្ចុប្បន្ននេះ វាគឺជាការវិនិច្ឆ័យរបស់យើងដែលថាពេលវេលារៀបចំផែនការសម្រាប់ចាក់ដូសជំរុញកូវីដគឺដល់ពេលហើយ។\r\nលោកបានបន្ថែមថា “នេះរួមបញ្ចូលទាំងពលរដ្ឋងាយរងគ្រោះបំផុតរបស់យើង ដូចជាអ្នកផ្តល់សេវាថែទាំសុខភាព អ្នកថែទាំផ្ទះ និងមនុស្សចាស់ដទៃទៀត។ យើងក៏នឹងចាប់ផ្តើមចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសជំរុញដោយផ្ទាល់ដល់អ្នករស់នៅមណ្ឌលថែទាំរយៈពេលវែងផងដែរ”។\r\nមន្រ្តីសុខាភិបាលបាននិយាយថា ពលរដ្ឋដែលបានចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងបង្ការប្រភេទចាក់មួយដូស Johnson & Johnson ទំនងជាត្រូវការការចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសបន្ថែមដើម្បីពន្យាប្រសិទ្ធភាពបង្ការឆ្លងមេរោគកូរ៉ូណា និងកាត់បន្ថយការឈឺធ្ងន់ធ្ងរពីអាការៈរោគសញ្ញាកូវីដ-១៩។ ទោះយ៉ាងណាក៏ដោយ ពួកគេកំពុងធ្វើការស្រាវជ្រាវ និងមិនទាន់បង្ហាញពីផែនការចាក់ដូសជំរុញដល់ក្រុមមនុស្សដែលបានចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងប្រភេទនេះនៅឡើយទេ។\r\nសហរដ្ឋអាមេរិកដែលជាប្រទេសដំបូងគេនៅលើពិភពលោកដែលចាប់ផ្តើមចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងបង្ការជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ ទើបតែសម្រេចចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងបង្ការដូសជំរុញជាផ្លូវការនៅដើមសប្តាហ៍នេះ ខណៈវ៉ាក់សាំង PfizerBiontech និង Moderna របស់ខ្លួន ដែលជាវ៉ាក់សាំងត្រូវប្រើជាចម្បងនៅសហរដ្ឋអាមេរិកបង្ហាញពីការបាត់បង់ប្រសិទ្ធភាពយ៉ាងខ្លាំង ក្រោយពីចាក់រួចរយៈពេល ៦ ខែ។\r\nការចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំង Pfizer និង Moderna ដូសជំរុញបង្ការជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ ត្រូវបានកំណត់ចាក់ឱ្យគ្រប់ពលរដ្ឋអាមេរិកពេញវ័យទាំងអស់ ដោយចាប់ផ្តើមនៅខែក្រោយ។\r\nវេជ្ជបណ្ឌិត Vivek Murthy គ្រូពេទ្យវះកាត់ទូទៅបាននិយាយនៅឯសន្និសីទកាសែតនៅសេតវិមានថា “យើងដឹងថាសូម្បីវ៉ាក់សាំងដែលមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពខ្ពស់ ក៏បាត់បង់មិនសូវមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពតាមពេលវេលាដែរ។ បច្ចុប្បន្ននេះ វាគឺជាការវិនិច្ឆ័យរបស់យើងដែលថាពេលវេលារៀបចំផែនការសម្រាប់ចាក់ដូសជំរុញកូវីដគឺដល់ពេលហើយ”។\r\nលោកបានបន្ថែមថា “នេះរួមបញ្ចូលទាំងពលរដ្ឋងាយរងគ្រោះបំផុតរបស់យើង ដូចជាអ្នកផ្តល់សេវាថែទាំសុខភាព អ្នកថែទាំផ្ទះ និងមនុស្សចាស់ដទៃទៀត។ យើងក៏នឹងចាប់ផ្តើមចាក់វ៉ាក់សាំងដូសជំរុញដោយផ្ទាល់ដល់អ្នករស់នៅមណ្ឌលថែទាំរយៈពេលវែងផងដែរ” ។\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nករណីឆ្លងប្រចាំថ្ងៃនៅកម្ពុជាបន្តធ្លាក់ ខណៈករណីឆ្លងនៅខេត្តបន្តកើន\r\n\r\n\r\nថ្ងៃនេះកម្ពុជាបានប្រកាសជាផ្លូវការនូវករណីឆ្លងថ្មីសរុបចំនួន ៥១៩ ករណីដែលធ្វើឱ្យករណីឆ្លងសរុបកើនដល់ ៨៨.២៤២ ករណី។ បច្ចុប្បន្ន ករណីឆ្លងក្នុងសហគមន៍សរុបមានចំនួន ៧៤.៤៣៨ ករណី និង ករណីនាំចូលសរុបមានចំនួន ១៣.៨០៤ ករណី។\r\nករណីនាំចូលថ្មីចំនួន ១៨៥ ករណីត្រូវបានប្រកាសនៅថ្ងៃនេះ ខណៈចំនួនករណីនាំចូលបន្តកើនឡើងខ្ពស់ ដោយសារផលវិបាកនៃការបើកព្រំដែនថៃឡើងវិញកាលពីសប្តាហ៍មុន។\r\nករណីឆ្លងតាមបណ្តាខេត្តបន្តកើនឡើងដែលបង្ហាញថា ខេត្តនានាជាពិសេសខេត្តទាំង៨ជាប់នឹងប្រទេសថៃ គឺស្ថិតនៅក្នុងជួរមុខនៃការប្រយុទ្ធប្រឆាំងនឹងជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ របស់កម្ពុជា។\r\nជាពិសេសខេត្តបន្ទាយមានជ័យបច្ចុប្បន្នកំពុងជួបប្រទះករណីឆ្លងកើនឡើង ដោយមានព័ត៌មានថា ក្រៅពីករណីឆ្លង ៦០១ ករណីដែលត្រូវបានរកឃើញនៅមណ្ឌលព្យាបាលអ្នកញៀនថ្នាំក្នុងខេត្តនេះ មានករណីចំនួន ៣១៤ ផ្សេងទៀតត្រូវបានរកឃើញកាលពីម្សិលមិញផងដែរ ដែលបង្ហាញថា ការកើនឡើងយ៉ាងខ្លាំងនៃករណីឆ្លងថ្មីកំពុងបន្ត។\r\nប្រហែលជាគួរឱ្យភ្ញាក់ផ្អើល នៅពេលលោកនាយករដ្ឋមន្ត្រីហ៊ុន សែនបានប្រកាសបញ្ចប់យុទ្ធនាការពង្រឹងវិធានការប្រឆាំងនឹងជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ នៅទូទាំងប្រទេស កាលពីយប់មិញ ខណៈសាលារាជធានីភ្នំពេញក៏បានបញ្ចប់បំរាមគោចរដែលបានអនុវត្តរយៈពេល ២១ ថ្ងៃ ផងដែរ។\r\nដោយឡែក ប្រទេសកម្ពុជាក៏បានប្រកាសពីការស្លាប់របស់អ្នកជំងឺថ្មីចំនួន ១៥ នាក់ដែលធ្វើឱ្យចំនួនសរុបនៃអ្នកស្លាប់ដល់ទៅ ១.៧៦២នាក់ នៅកម្ពុជា។ ការជាសះស្បើយឡើងវិញរបស់អ្នកជំងឺថ្មីចំនួន ៥៥៣នាក់ ត្រូវបានប្រកាសនៅថ្ងៃនេះ នេះមានន័យថា ចំនួនសរុបនៃអ្នកកំពុងសំរាកព្យាបាល បានធ្លាក់ចុះមកត្រឹម ២.៦២២នាក់៕\r\n', 'dreamstime_m_209946214-360x245.jpg', 4, NULL, '2021-08-21 10:40:04'),
(34, 'Rice production beats rainy season target', 'Rainy season rice production in Cambodia has already exceeded its target yield, according to Agriculture minister Veng Sakhon.', 'As of this week farmers had grown more than 2.6 million tonnes, nearly 102 percent of the yearly plan. The amount of ‘light rice’ harvested during the early rainy season rose to nearly 1.3 million tonnes, a year-on-year increase of more than 789,000 tonnes, for an average yield per hectare of 4.2 tonnes. Last year the harvest fell 5 percent short of its target.\r\nNot every farm has benefited from the seasonal rains. Nearly 68,000 hectares of rice paddies in the provinces of Banteay Meanchey, Kandal, Pursat, and Siem Reap were hit by drought. The drought-stricken areas account for 2.6 percent of the country’s rice fields.\r\nOther crops performed worse than rice. Subsidiary crops (white corn, sweet potatoes, vegetables, chili and watermelon) were 4 percent short of their annual target. Industrial crops such as red corn, cassava, beans, peanuts, soybeans, sesame, and sugarcane fell 7 percent short of projected yields.\r\n\r\nOther crops performed worse than rice. Subsidiary crops (white corn, sweet potatoes, vegetables, chili and watermelon) were 4 percent short of their annual target. Industrial crops such as red corn, cassava, beans, peanuts, soybeans, sesame, and sugarcane fell 7 percent short of projected yields.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '19.jpg', 3, NULL, '2021-08-21 10:44:01'),
(35, 'Vehicle registrations drop as Covid cuts car sales', 'Vehicle registrations fell 7 percent in the first half of this year, compared with the same period in 2020. The drop came as the Coronavirus pandemic weighed on sentiment and consumers put off purchases. ', 'Vehicle registrations fell 7 percent in the first half of this year, compared with the same period in 2020. The drop came as the Coronavirus pandemic weighed on sentiment and consumers put off purchases. Travel restrictions also made it harder to get to registration centres.\r\nNearly 250,000 vehicles were registered from January through June according to Chhuon Vorn, director-general of the transport ministry’s general department of land transport.\r\nTo encourage more people to get their paperwork in order, Vorn says the transport ministry is adding public service centres in some provincial capitals. In Phnom Penh drivers can register their vehicles at the two Aeon Malls, Chip Mong Mall and the ministry’s own centre. In Siem Reap, there is an office at Heritage Walk.\r\nFrom 1990 to the end of June 2021, the department of land transport registered 6.1 million vehicles, including 5 million motorcycles.\r\nCar importers say shipments have dropped since the start of the Coronavirus pandemic. They say falling incomes have curbed luxury car sales. Car imports fell 10 percent last year compared with 2019.\r\n', 'IMG_7014-1-360x245.jpg', 1, NULL, '2021-08-21 10:53:18'),
(36, 'Chelsea: How to unearth the best version of Kai Havertz', 'Throughout his Leverkusen career, Havertz was pushed further and further up the pitch as his attacking talents came to fruition. But where he grew into the player that Chelsea paid all that money for was right at the top, whi', 'Throughout his Leverkusen career, Havertz was pushed further and further up the pitch as his attacking talents came to fruition.But where he grew into the player that Chelsea paid all that money for was right at the top, whilst being allowed to drop back and create.In 2019/20, when Havertz played up top predominantly, he scored 17 goals, eight assists with 2.2 key passes per 90 at 85.4% passing accuracy.When played in this position by Chelsea, he scored a hattrick in the FA Cup and scored in two Premier League games.Havertz can bring a lot to the table, but if you want the most out of his goal-scoring and creating abilities, that false nine allows him to flourish.Havertz also has a lot of versatility too: In 2018/19, he played more at attacking midfield and still scored 17 goals, but amassed only 5 assists and averaged just one key pass per 90.With the young German very clearly having talents at both positions, the false nine combines both and is where he has shown his best performances in Germany and in his short time at Chelsea.', 'Manchester-City-v-Chelsea-FC---UEFA-Champions-Leag-d4d96197a4f16591e9195f2fcc9520eb.jpg', 2, NULL, '2021-08-21 11:01:22'),
(37, 'ករណីឆ្លងប្រចាំថ្ងៃនៅកម្ពុជាបន្តធ្លាក់ ខណៈករណីឆ្លងនៅខេត្តបន្តកើន', 'ថ្ងៃនេះកម្ពុជាបានប្រកាសជាផ្លូវការនូវករណីឆ្លងថ្មីសរុបចំនួន ៥១៩ ករណីដែលធ្វើឱ្យករណីឆ្លងសរុបកើនដល់ ៨៨.២៤២ ករណី។ បច្ចុប្បន្ន ករណីឆ្លងក្នុងសហគមន៍សរុបមានចំនួន ៧៤.៤៣៨ ករណី និង ករណីនាំចូលសរុបមានចំនួន ១៣.៨០៤ ករណី។', 'ថ្ងៃនេះកម្ពុជាបានប្រកាសជាផ្លូវការនូវករណីឆ្លងថ្មីសរុបចំនួន ៥១៩ ករណីដែលធ្វើឱ្យករណីឆ្លងសរុបកើនដល់ ៨៨.២៤២ ករណី។ បច្ចុប្បន្ន ករណីឆ្លងក្នុងសហគមន៍សរុបមានចំនួន ៧៤.៤៣៨ ករណី និង ករណីនាំចូលសរុបមានចំនួន ១៣.៨០៤ ករណី។\r\nករណីនាំចូលថ្មីចំនួន ១៨៥ ករណីត្រូវបានប្រកាសនៅថ្ងៃនេះ ខណៈចំនួនករណីនាំចូលបន្តកើនឡើងខ្ពស់ ដោយសារផលវិបាកនៃការបើកព្រំដែនថៃឡើងវិញកាលពីសប្តាហ៍មុន។\r\nករណីឆ្លងតាមបណ្តាខេត្តបន្តកើនឡើងដែលបង្ហាញថា ខេត្តនានាជាពិសេសខេត្តទាំង៨ជាប់នឹងប្រទេសថៃ គឺស្ថិតនៅក្នុងជួរមុខនៃការប្រយុទ្ធប្រឆាំងនឹងជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ របស់កម្ពុជា។\r\nជាពិសេសខេត្តបន្ទាយមានជ័យបច្ចុប្បន្នកំពុងជួបប្រទះករណីឆ្លងកើនឡើង ដោយមានព័ត៌មានថា ក្រៅពីករណីឆ្លង ៦០១ ករណីដែលត្រូវបានរកឃើញនៅមណ្ឌលព្យាបាលអ្នកញៀនថ្នាំក្នុងខេត្តនេះ មានករណីចំនួន ៣១៤ ផ្សេងទៀតត្រូវបានរកឃើញកាលពីម្សិលមិញផងដែរ ដែលបង្ហាញថា ការកើនឡើងយ៉ាងខ្លាំងនៃករណីឆ្លងថ្មីកំពុងបន្ត។\r\nប្រហែលជាគួរឱ្យភ្ញាក់ផ្អើល នៅពេលលោកនាយករដ្ឋមន្ត្រីហ៊ុន សែនបានប្រកាសបញ្ចប់យុទ្ធនាការពង្រឹងវិធានការប្រឆាំងនឹងជំងឺកូវីដ-១៩ នៅទូទាំងប្រទេស កាលពីយប់មិញ ខណៈសាលារាជធានីភ្នំពេញក៏បានបញ្ចប់បំរាមគោចរដែលបានអនុវត្តរយៈពេល ២១ ថ្ងៃ ផងដែរ។\r\nដោយឡែក ប្រទេសកម្ពុជាក៏បានប្រកាសពីការស្លាប់របស់អ្នកជំងឺថ្មីចំនួន ១៥ នាក់ដែលធ្វើឱ្យចំនួនសរុបនៃអ្នកស្លាប់ដល់ទៅ ១.៧៦២នាក់ នៅកម្ពុជា។ ការជាសះស្បើយឡើងវិញរបស់អ្នកជំងឺថ្មីចំនួន ៥៥៣នាក់ ត្រូវបានប្រកាសនៅថ្ងៃនេះ នេះមានន័យថា ចំនួនសរុបនៃអ្នកកំពុងសំរាកព្យាបាល បានធ្លាក់ចុះមកត្រឹម ២.៦២២នាក់៕\r\n', 'dreamstime_m_182748298-002-360x245.jpg', 4, NULL, '2021-08-21 11:07:57'),
(38, 'Agriculture, forestry, and fishing', 'Agriculture remains the most important sector of the Cambodian economy in terms of its share of the gross domestic product (GDP), and it employs the vast majority of the workforce. Rice is Cambodia’s major crop, its principal', 'Agriculture remains the most important sector of the Cambodian economy in terms of its share of the gross domestic product (GDP), and it employs the vast majority of the workforce. Rice is Cambodia’s major crop, its principal food, and, in times of peace, its most important export commodity. Rice is grown on most of the country’s total cultivated land area. The principal rice regions surround the Mekong and the Tonle Sap, with particularly intensive cultivation in Bătdâmbâng, Kâmpóng Cham, Takêv, and Prey Vêng provinces.\r\nCambodia traditionally has produced only one rice crop per year because it has lacked the extensive irrigation system needed for double-cropping. Under traditional patterns of agriculture, planting normally begins in July or August, and the harvest period extends from November to January. Where there is little irrigation, the amount of rainfall determines the size and quality of the crop.\r\nThe government of Democratic Kampuchea made great efforts to build irrigation systems throughout the country. The results occasionally were notable, and in a few parts of the country farmers were able to grow two or, more rarely, three crops of rice per year. In some cases the irrigation works were poorly conceived and hastily built, and they soon collapsed. Most of those that survived were abandoned after 1979. Another significant problem is that millions of land mines remain in Cambodian fields from the years of warfare; this has severely restricted the amount of land available for cultivation.\r\nIn addition to rice, other food products include cassava, corn (maize), sugarcane, soybeans, and coconuts. The principal fruit crops, all of which are consumed locally, include bananas, oranges, and mangoes, and are supplemented by a variety of other tropical fruits, including breadfruits, mangosteens, and papayas.\r\nCattle, particularly water buffalo, are used principally as draft animals in the rice paddies and fields. Hog production has also played a large role in agriculture. Efforts to replenish the number of livestock—depleted by years of war—have been hampered by uncertain social conditions and the prevalence of animal diseases.\r\nAbout three-fourths of Cambodia was forested in 1970, but by the early 21st century that portion had decreased to roughly half, with Cambodia carrying one of the highest deforestation rates in the world. The provinces bordering Thailand and Vietnam continue to be logged by large companies to whom the government has granted concessions, as well as by smaller entrepreneurs, many of whom do not obtain official permits. Illegal logging is a persistent and serious problem despite efforts to curb it.\r\nFisheries are important in the domestic economy. Fish in its various forms—fresh, dried, smoked, and salted—constitutes the most important source of protein in the Cambodian diet, and subsistence fishing is part of every farmer’s activity. The annual freshwater catch includes perch, carp, lungfish, and smelt. For larger-scale fishing, the government sells two-year leases to harvest segments of the Tonle Sap and inland rivers. Revenues from these sales have been significant at times, but the program has been fraught with corruption. Overfishing and environmental degradation around Tonle Sap have decreased the fish supply and driven up prices, and the sustainability of freshwater fisheries has become a matter of public concern.\r\n', 'Farmer-cattle-Cambodia.jpg', 3, NULL, '2021-08-21 11:17:11'),
(39, 'Community outbreak alters job outlook for the Kingdom’s youth', '  With the government announcing yesterday that it is temporarily freezing the recruitment of civil servants and a large number of overseas workers returning from abroad, the job prospects for young Cambodians has drastically', ' With the government announcing yesterday that it is temporarily freezing the recruitment of civil servants and a large number of overseas workers returning from abroad, the job prospects for young Cambodians has drastically altered.\r\n\r\nPalin provincial Governor Ban Sreymom previously said the slew of returning migrant workers is straining the province’s logistics network as workers are “not just returning from Thailand, they are literally moving house, bringing everything with them”.\r\nEan Sreyleak, 22, graduated in December 2019, just before the pandemic struck. She said that she decided to take a break before applying for jobs because she had been taking undergraduate degrees at two different universities concurrently.\r\n“When I first graduated, human resource representatives from different companies used to message me all the time on LinkedIn but that began to go down during 2020 and now I’m hardly receiving messages after the community outbreak,” she told Khmer Times.\r\nSreyleak now works as an auditor. She said that many young people eagerly anticipated entering the workforce immediately after graduating from university but had difficulty finding jobs.\r\nOnce some did manage to gain employment, many were almost immediately furloughed, found their pay cut by half or were told they had to work from home.\r\n“I think that the employment situation depends heavily on your major. If you studied something like hospitality or tourism then you will have a much harder time than someone who majored in IT [information technology], finance or banking,” she said.\r\nShe also noted that some people have opted to stay at home entirely if their family’s financial situation allows for it.\r\nA close friend of hers has not applied for work since graduating because the family is believed to be financially stable and prefers that their daughter not work in an office during the pandemic.\r\nShe added that she had originally planned to further her studies abroad but those plans have been laid to rest temporarily because of the pandemic.\r\n“Studying is just one part of going to another country for education. But now it will all be virtual and you won’t have the chance to travel or visit other countries so I think it is best to just work right now,” she added.\r\nSamreth Haripong, a final-year law student, 21, said that he had also  planned on studying abroad after graduating – preferably in northern or western European countries such as Germany, Norway or the Netherlands.\r\nSamreth quoted Chanika Mitchell, his former political science and global affairs professor who spent some time living in South Korea, as saying, “In South Korea, the citizens tend to have an inward view in how they want to live their lives in their own country. In contrast, Cambodian citizens tend to have an outward view of the rest of the world, not an inward view of their own country.”\r\n', '25484-360x245.jpg', 1, NULL, '2021-08-21 11:28:48'),
(40, 'Machine Lewandowski just too Gerd to be true', 'Robert Lewandowski, dubbed a machine by his wife, has added the Bundesliga record for most goals in a season to the long list of major honors and achievements he has claimed in his illustrious career.', 'Robert Lewandowski, dubbed a machine by his wife, has added the Bundesliga record for most goals in a season to the long list of major honors and achievements he has claimed in his illustrious career.\r\nGerd Muellers mark of 40 goals in a campaign, set in the 1971-72 season, had stood the test of time until Lewandowski converted a first-half penalty for Bayern Munich in a 2-2 draw at Freiburg on Saturday.\r\nWhile Mueller set his record over 34 league games, Lewandowski has scored his 40 goals in 28 matches, due to a knee injury last month and squad rotation.\r\nIts a huge honor for me and for the modern history of the Bundesliga, Lewandowski told Sky.\r\nAs part of his penalty celebrations, the Poland striker lifted his match shirt to reveal a picture of the legendary Mueller accompanied by the message 4ever Gerd\r\nI would never have thought that this would happen. What Gerd Mueller did is incredible. Sharing the record with him makes me very, very proud,\" Lewandowski added.\r\nThe fixture was briefly halted after Lewandowski scored as his Bayern teammates formed a guard of honor on the side of the pitch which the smiling 32-year-old ran through.\r\nLewandowski has scored five Bundesliga hat-tricks this term, including a four-goal haul in a 4-3 win over Hertha Berlin in October.\r\n', '60a1c13ea31024adbdc8162b.jpeg', 2, NULL, '2021-08-21 11:33:47'),
(41, 'កិច្ចពិភាក្សាថ្នាក់រដ្ឋមន្ត្រីនៅថ្ងៃនេះ ស្តីពីដំណើរការសកម្មភាពឡើងវិញក្រោយពីកូវីដជាមួយវិស័យទេសចរណ៍', 'រដ្ឋមន្ត្រីក្រសួងទេសចរណ៍កំពុងជួបពិភាក្សាជាមួយតំណាងឧស្សាហកម្មនៅថ្ងៃនេះ (ថ្ងៃសុក្រ) ។ នេះគឺជាកិច្ចប្រជុំដំបូងដែលរៀបចំឡើងដើម្បីត្រៀមទទួលភ្ញៀវទេសចរអន្តរជាតិ នៅពេលដែលមេរោគកូរ៉ូណាត្រូវបានគ្រប់គ្រង។', 'រដ្ឋមន្ត្រីក្រសួងទេសចរណ៍កំពុងជួបពិភាក្សាជាមួយតំណាងឧស្សាហកម្មនៅថ្ងៃនេះ (ថ្ងៃសុក្រ) ។ នេះគឺជាកិច្ចប្រជុំដំបូងដែលរៀបចំឡើងដើម្បីត្រៀមទទួលភ្ញៀវទេសចរអន្តរជាតិ នៅពេលដែលមេរោគកូរ៉ូណាត្រូវបានគ្រប់គ្រង។\r\nកិច្ចពិភាក្សានេះក៏នឹងពិនិត្យមើលផងដែរថាតើធ្វើដូចម្តេចដើម្បីទទួលបានផលចំណេញពីកំណើនភ្ញៀវទេសចរក្នុងស្រុកដែលកំពុងចាប់ផ្តើមមានសកម្មភាពជុំវិញប្រទេសម្តងទៀត។ វាអាចមានហេតុផលសុទិដ្ឋិនិយមខ្លះ ចំពោះការវិលត្រឡប់មករកភាពប្រក្រតីវិញ។ កាលពីយប់មិញសាលារាជធានីភ្នំពេញបានប្រកាសថាខ្លួននឹងបញ្ចប់បម្រាមគោចរចាប់ពីម៉ោង ១០ យប់ដល់ម៉ោង ៣ ទៀបភ្លឺ ទោះបីជាការរឹតត្បិតផ្សេងទៀតនៅបន្តមានក៏ដោយ។\r\nក្រុមការងារនេះត្រូវបានបង្កើតឡើងកាលពីខែមុន។ តំណាងមកពីក្រសួងនឹងជួបជាមួយតំណាងវិស័យឯកជនចំនួន ៤៣ នាក់។ ពួកគេនឹងមានឱកាសផ្តល់ធាតុចូលលើផែនទីបង្ហាញផ្លូវរបស់រដ្ឋាភិបាលសម្រាប់ការងើបឡើងវិញនៃឧស្សាហកម្មទេសចរណ៍។ លោកនាយករដ្ឋមន្រ្តី ហ៊ុន សែន មានប្រសាសន៍ថា ប្រសិនបើផែនទីបង្ហាញផ្លូវត្រូវបានអនុវត្តតាម ប្រទេសអាចទទួលបានទេសចរអន្តរជាតិចំនួន ៧ លាននាក់ នៅត្រឹមឆ្នាំ ២០២៥ ។\r\nនៅឆ្នាំ ២០១៩ មានភ្ញៀវទេសចរបរទេសជាង ៦.៦ លាននាក់បានមកកម្ពុជាដែលបានរួមចំណែកជិត ២០% នៃផលិតផលក្នុងស្រុកសរុប។ ការមកដល់របស់ភ្ញៀវទេសចរកាលពីឆ្នាំមុនបានធ្លាក់ចុះដល់ ១.៣ លាននាក់ ដែលរួមចំណែកបានត្រឹមតែ ៣% នៃទំហំសេដ្ឋកិច្ចប៉ុណ្ណោះ។\r\nលោក Arnaud Darc ប្រធានសមាគមភោជនីយដ្ឋានកម្ពុជា បានមានប្រសាសន៍ថា “យើងមិនអាចរង់ចាំជំងឺរាតត្បាតនេះចប់ទេ ដោយសារមេរោគនេះទំនងជាមិនចេញពីយើងឡើយ យើងគ្មានជម្រើសក្រៅពីបន្តរស់នៅ ធ្វើការ និងរៀនសូត្រជាមួយវាទេ”៕\r\n', '11-5-360x245.jpg', 4, NULL, '2021-08-21 11:45:31'),
(42, 'The good vegetables that we need to eat, for get energy to get the power for feed our is the good for health', 'Agriculture remains the most important sector of the Cambodian economy in terms of its share of the gross domestic product (GDP), and it employs the vast majority of the workforce. Rice is Cambodia’s major crop, its principal', 'Agriculture remains the most important sector of the Cambodian economy in terms of its share of the gross domestic product (GDP), and it employs the vast majority of the workforce. Rice is Cambodia’s major crop, its principal food, and, in times of peace, its most important export commodity. Rice is grown on most of the country’s total cultivated land area. The principal rice regions surround the Mekong and the Tonle Sap, with particularly intensive cultivation in Bătdâmbâng, Kâmpóng Cham, Takêv, and Prey Vêng provinces.Cambodia traditionally has produced only one rice crop per year because it has lacked the extensive irrigation system needed for double-cropping. Under traditional patterns of agriculture, planting normally begins in July or August, and the harvest period extends from November to January. Where there is little irrigation, the amount of rainfall determines the size and quality of the crop.The government of Democratic Kampuchea made great efforts to build irrigation systems throughout the country. The results occasionally were notable, and in a few parts of the country farmers were able to grow two or, more rarely, three crops of rice per year. In some cases the irrigation works were poorly conceived and hastily built, and they soon collapsed. Most of those that survived were abandoned after 1979. Another significant problem is that millions of land mines remain in Cambodian fields from the years of warfare; this has severely restricted the amount of land available for cultivation.In addition to rice, other food products include cassava, corn (maize), sugarcane, soybeans, and coconuts. The principal fruit crops, all of which are consumed locally, include bananas, oranges, and mangoes, and are supplemented by a variety of other tropical fruits, including breadfruits, mangosteens, and papayas.Cattle, particularly water buffalo, are used principally as draft animals in the rice paddies and fields. Hog production has also played a large role in agriculture. Efforts to replenish the number of livestock—depleted by years of war—have been hampered by uncertain social conditions and the prevalence of animal diseases.About three-fourths of Cambodia was forested in 1970, but by the early 21st century that portion had decreased to roughly half, with Cambodia carrying one of the highest deforestation rates in the world. The provinces bordering Thailand and Vietnam continue to be logged by large companies to whom the government has granted concessions, as well as by smaller entrepreneurs, many of whom do not obtain official permits. Illegal logging is a persistent and serious problem despite efforts to curb it.Fisheries are important in the domestic economy. Fish in its various forms—fresh, dried, smoked, and salted—constitutes the most important source of protein in the Cambodian diet, and subsistence fishing is part of every farmer’s activity. The annual freshwater catch includes perch, carp, lungfish, and smelt. For larger-scale fishing, the government sells two-year leases to harvest segments of the Tonle Sap and inland rivers. Revenues from these sales have been significant at times, but the program has been fraught with corruption. Overfishing and environmental degradation around Tonle Sap have decreased the fish supply and driven up prices, and the sustainability of freshwater fisheries has become a matter of public concern.', 'product-jpeg-500x500.jpg', 3, NULL, '2021-08-21 12:04:07'),
(43, 'ABA files Q2 report highlighted by strong income/profit growth', 'Advanced Bank of Asia Ltd (ABA) has filed a second quarter report showing continued advances quarter-by-quarter and year-on-year, as it positions itself as the leading retail bank in the Kingdom. The wholly Canadian owned fir', 'Advanced Bank of Asia Ltd (ABA) has filed a second quarter report showing continued advances quarter-by-quarter and year-on-year, as it positions itself as the leading retail bank in the Kingdom.\r\nThe wholly Canadian owned firm, which shares the same brand look and feel of its parent company (National Bank of Canada) saw its Q2 2021 total income rise nearly 33 percent over Q2 2020 results.\r\nABAs total second quarter income reached roughly $122,959,063. Net profit for Q2 2021 was recorded at $45,334,111. This represented a huge increase over Q2 2020 $24,898,384.\r\nThe banks non-performing loan (NPL) ratio for the period barely moved, going from 0.7 percent at the end of the Q2 2020 reporting period to 0.78 percent for the second quarter of 2021, an impressive feat that perhaps says more about ABA borrowers than anything else given the bank’s strong commitment to support National Bank of Cambodia guidelines.\r\nABA assets grew to $6,966,977,458 from Q2 2020s $6,081,603,605, up 14.1 percent as noted in the financial highlights page of its report.\r\nThe banks liabilities were also on the rise however, up 14.8 percent to $6,106,456,848.\r\nEquity grew to $860,520,610 in Q2 2021, a 12.9 percent hike according to the company over 2020 second quarter results.\r\nIn his message to shareholders, Yves Jacquot, chairman of the board of directors of ABA, cited a number of the year’s developments and highlights.\r\nJacquot said that as an active member of the business community, ABA provided feasible contributions to people and businesses of Cambodia, noting that in April, the bank donated $1 million to support government efforts in stopping the spread of the COVID virus.\r\nJacquot also wrote that the bank continued distributing new loans to its customers because access to capital is vital for people and businesses not only in the growing economy but also in times of crisis. ABA has maintained participation in the SME Co-Financing Scheme 2020 (SCFS), an initiative of Cambodia’s government to provide affordable loans to small and medium enterprises.\r\nSumming up ongoing plans, he added that ABA is continuing to implement its business strategy, focusing on digital finance products and productive loans to businesses in sectors of the economy. He emphasised the continuous innovating of banking solutions and application of a robust risk-management culture strengthened by audit and compliance functions.\r\nThe USD to riels currency conversions listed in this article were based on yesterday’s exchange rates.\r\nAs such they will show a variance with currency conversions executed with exchange rates recorded on the dates cited in the report’s compiling.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '25413.jpg', 1, NULL, '2021-08-21 12:21:29'),
(44, 'Robert Lewandowski breaks 49-year goal-scoring record with 41st goal of the season', 'Robert Lewandowski raises the top goal-scorer of the season award following the Bundesliga match between Bayern Munich and Augsburg. (CNN)He wouldve liked to have done it earlier in the day, but eventually, Robert Lewandowski', 'Robert Lewandowski, dubbed a machine by his wife, has added the Bundesliga record for most goals in a season to the long list of major honors and achievements he has claimed in his illustrious career. Gerd Muellers mark of 40 goals in a campaign, set in the 1971-72 season, had stood the test of time until Lewandowski converted a first-half penalty for Bayern Munich in a 2-2 draw at Freiburg on Saturday. While Mueller set his record over 34 league games, Lewandowski has scored his 40 goals in 28 matches, due to a knee injury last month and squad rotation. Its a huge honor for me and for the modern history of the Bundesliga, Lewandowski told Sky. As part of his penalty celebrations, the Poland striker lifted his match shirt to reveal a picture of the legendary Mueller accompanied by the message 4ever GerdThroughout his Leverkusen career, Havertz was pushed further and further up the pitch as his attacking talents came to fruition. But where he grew into the player that Chelsea paid all that money for was right at the top, whilst being allowed to drop back and create. In 2019/20, when Havertz played up top predominantly, he scored 17 goals, eight assists with 2.2 key passes per 90 at 85.4% passing accuracy. When played in this position by Chelsea, he scored a hattrick in the FA Cup and scored in two Premier League games. Havertz can bring a lot to the table, but if you want the most out of his goal-scoring and creating abilities, that false nine allows him to flourish. Havertz also has a lot of versatility too: In 2018/19, he played more at attacking midfield and still scored 17 goals, but amassed only 5 assists and averaged just one key pass per 90. With the young German very clearly having talents at both positions, the false nine combines both and is where he has shown his best performances in Germany and in his short time at Chelsea.', '210522122452-02-robert-lewandowski-0522-super-tease.jpg', 2, NULL, '2021-08-21 12:29:24'),
(45, 'កម្ពុជាបាននាំចេញរ៉ែ​មាសលើកដំបូង​ទៅបន្សុទ្ធនៅបរទេស', 'ក្រុមហ៊ុន Renaissance Minerals Cambodia Limited បានចាប់ផ្តើមដឹកជញ្ជូនរ៉ែមាសពីរោងចក្រចម្រាញ់រ៉ែមាសដែលមានទីតាំងស្ថិតនៅតំបន់អូរខ្វាវ ស្រុកកែវសីមា​ ខេត្តមណ្ឌលគិរីទៅបរទេស ដើម្បីធ្វើការ​បន្សុទ្ធបន្ថែមនៅបរទេស។ ការដឹកជញ្ជូននេះបានធ្វើ', 'ក្រុមហ៊ុន Renaissance Minerals Cambodia Limited បានចាប់ផ្តើមដឹកជញ្ជូនរ៉ែមាសពីរោងចក្រចម្រាញ់រ៉ែមាសដែលមានទីតាំងស្ថិតនៅតំបន់អូរខ្វាវ ស្រុកកែវសីមា​ ខេត្តមណ្ឌលគិរីទៅបរទេស ដើម្បីធ្វើការ​បន្សុទ្ធបន្ថែមនៅបរទេស។ ការដឹកជញ្ជូននេះបានធ្វើឡើងក្រោយរយៈពេលពីរខែនៃការចម្រាញ់រ៉ែមាសផ្លូវការដំបូង។\r\nលោក យស មុនីរ៉ាត់ អគ្គនាយកនៃអគ្គនាយកដ្ឋានធនធានរ៉ែនៃក្រសួងរ៉ែ និងថាមពលបានឲ្យដឹងថា៖ «យើងបានអនុវត្តការនាំចេញបានជាបណ្ដើរៗហើយនៅជើងទី ១ ចំនួន ៥៩ គីឡូក្រាមរួចហើយឥឡូវយើងកំពុងរៀបចំនាំចេញនៅជើងទី ២បន្តទៀត។ អញ្ចឹងយើងផលិតបានមកដល់ពេលនេះវាបានជាង ១០០ គីឡូក្រាមហើយគិតជាលេខមូល»។\r\n\r\nលោកបន្តថា៖ «យើងបាននាំទៅធ្វើការបន្សុទ្ធនៅក្នុងប្រទេសអូស្ត្រាលីដើម្បីឲ្យវាក្លាយ ទៅជាមាស ៩៩.៩៩ ហើយដាក់លក់នៅទីផ្សារអន្តរជាតិតែម្ដង»។\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nលោកកត់សម្គាល់ថាហាងឆេងមាសនៅទីផ្សារអន្តរជាតិបច្ចុប្បន្ន អាចប្រែប្រួលប្រចាំថៃ្ង ក្នុងតម្លៃ៥៨.០០០ដុល្លារ ក្នុងមួយគីឡូក្រាម។\r\n\r\nលោកបន្ថែមថា៖ «សម្រាប់ការដឹកជញ្ជូនរ៉ែមាសទម្ងន់ ១០០ គីឡូក្រាមលើកទី ២ បច្ចុប្បន្នក្រុមហ៊ុនកំពុងបំពេញបែបបទគយលើការនាំចេញដែលត្រូវបានគេរំពឹងថានឹងរួចរាល់ក្នុងពេលឆាប់ៗនេះ»។\r\n\r\nប្រតិបត្តិការជាផ្លូវការនៃការធ្វើអាជីវកម្មរ៉ែមាសពាណិជ្ជកម្មលើកដំបូងរបស់កម្ពុជាបានចាប់ផ្តើមនៅខែមិថុនាឆ្នាំនេះ។ ចាប់តាំងពីការចាប់ផ្តើមប្រតិបត្តិការ កម្ពុជាចម្រាញ់មាសបានជាង ២១០ គីឡូក្រាមហើយ។\r\n\r\nក្រសួងរំពឹង​ថាការដ្ឋាន​អាជីវកម្ម​ និង​រោងចក្រ​ចម្រាញ់​រ៉ែ​មាស​នេះមាន​សមត្ថភាព​ជីក​យក​រ៉ែ​ឆៅប្រមាណ ​៣​ តោន​ក្នុង​មួយឆ្នាំសម្រាប់​រយៈ​ពេល​ប៉ាន់ស្មាន ៨​ ឆ្នាំ​ដំបូង។\r\n\r\nលោក យស មុនីរ៉ាត់ បានលើកឡើងថា៖ «កម្ពុជានឹងទទួលចំណូលពីសួយសារ ៣% នៃចំណូលដែលលក់ដុលបានសរុប»។\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nកម្ពុជារំពឹងថានឹងទទួលបាន ​ចំណូល​សួយ​សារ និង​សារ​ពើ​ពន្ធ​ផ្ទាល់​មាន​ប្រមាណ ​៤០ ​លាន​ដុល្លា​អាមេរិក​ក្នុង​មួយ​ឆ្នាំទៅរកថវិកាជាតិ។\r\n\r\nលោកនិយាយថា៖ «ក្រុមហ៊ុន Renaissance បាន​សិក្សា​និង​វាយ​តម្លៃគ្រប់​ជ្រុងជ្រោយ ​ពី​ផល​ប៉ះ​ពាល់​បរិស្ថាននិង​សង្គម​នៃ​អាជីវកម្ម​ធនធាន​រ៉ែ​នេះ អស់​រយៈ​ពេល​ជិត​១៤​ ឆ្នាំ។ នៅពេលដាក់ឲ្យ​ដំណើរការ​នេះ លោកនាយករដ្ឋមន្រ្តី ហ៊ុន សែន បានអំពាវនាវកុំឲ្យប្រជាពលរដ្ឋប្រព្រឹត្តអំពើខុសច្បាប់លើការជីកយករ៉ែមាស ដោយកត់សម្គាល់ថាដំណើរការនេះត្រូវការអ្នកជំនាញបច្ចេកទេសឧបករណ៍ និងស្តង់ដារពិសេស។ គន្លងមក ធ្លាប់មានមនុស្សជាច្រើនបានមកជីករ៉ែមាសនៅក្នុងតំបន់នេះ»។\r\n\r\nលោកបន្តថា៖ «ចំពោះអាជីវកម្មខុសច្បាប់របស់ប្រជាជននៅក្នុងតំបន់ក្រុមហ៊ុនអាជ្ញាប័ណ្ណ​ Renaissance បានសហការជាមួយអាជ្ញាធរដើម្បីដោះស្រាយលើគោលនយោបាយដើម្បីឲ្យពួកគេចាកចេញ»៕', 'photo_2021-08-18_18-51-09-360x245.jpg', 4, NULL, '2021-08-21 12:34:38'),
(46, 'Tencent sales growth slows as China crackdown weighs', 'AFP – Chinese tech giant Tencent’s revenue grew at its slowest pace in two years, results released this week showed, as it and other gaming firms now brace for an expected regulatory crackdown.', 'AFP – Chinese tech giant Tencent’s revenue grew at its slowest pace in two years, results released this week showed, as it and other gaming firms now brace for an expected regulatory crackdown.\r\nTotal revenues came in at $42.3 billion for the first half of 2021, up 23 percent year-on-year while operating profits were up 17 percent.\r\nSales rose 20 percent to $21.3 billion for the second quarter while mobile games sales grew 13 percent.\r\nWhile the figures remain healthy, the growth rate has slowed closer to pre-pandemic levels.\r\nGaming giants saw a boom in profits over the last year as Coronavirus swept the globe and kept consumers at home.\r\nBut Chinese gaming firms now face new headwinds.\r\nThe Chinese government has been cracking down on Big Tech and other powerful sectors deemed to be out of control with signs gaming is next in the firing line.\r\nThe online gaming industry, which made revenue of $20 billion in the first half of this year, has been the subject of several menacing state media reports in recent days, with one article labelling such games “spiritual opium”.\r\nThe negative headlines have fuelled concerns the sector is next in line for the regulatory axe, which has cut into large tech firms from e-commerce behemoth Alibaba to ride-hailing giant Didi Chuxing, hammering share prices.\r\nLast month, regulators ordered Tencents music arm to relinquish exclusive licensing deals with a number of labels and quashed a potential merger of two rival game streaming platforms.\r\nEarlier this month Tencent dropped bombshell curbs on play time, an early sign of broader industry changes to come.\r\nPlayers under the age of 12, for example, can no longer make in-game purchases in multiplayer battle smash-hit Honor of Kings, while under-18s are locked out after two hours during holidays and one hour on school nights.\r\n', '25469.jpg', 1, NULL, '2021-08-21 13:22:50'),
(47, 'Cambodia and Japan in talks to promote agro-tourism and recovery ', 'In a video discussion on August 12 chaired by the Director General of Tourism Development and International Cooperation, Thong Rathsak, with the Second Secretary ', 'Cambodia and Japan discussed the promotion of the agro-tourism subsector and the development and restoration of the tourism sector after the end of the Covid-19 pandemic.In a video discussion on August 12 chaired by the Director General of Tourism Development and International Cooperation, Thong Rathsak, with the Second Secretary in charge of Agriculture from the Japanese Embassy, Okada Naoya, and the founder of Yamato Green, Nabeshima Katsuhito, discussed the preparation for agrotourism projects in order to facilitate the recovery of the tourism industry in Cambodia after the end of the pandemic. The recovery is jto be promoted by development of new agro-tourism products, the Green Belt, as well as promote value added in tourism.The Ministry of Tourism signed a memorandum of understanding with Yamato Green in September 2020 with the aim of promoting the development of the Green Belt Project. The project focuses on the development of agro-tourism, eco-tourism, and community tourism in the Kingdom.Through this cooperation the Ministry of Tourism has been preparing a pilot project on agro-tourism and modern techniques of cultivation in Baray District, Kampong Thom. The project’s goal is to study and gradually evolve the agro-tourism sector through the cultivation of vegetables and fruits in compliance to modern food safety standards. It also aims to inspire and facilitate the livelihood of the locals.', 'Japan-Cambodia-agro-tourism1572-360x245.jpg', 3, NULL, '2021-08-21 13:26:53'),
(48, 'Champions League final – Man City vs Chelsea: As it happened', 'Thomas Tuchel: “This is unbelievable. To share it with everybody is unbelievable. I don’t know what to feel. The players were determined to win this.”', 'Thomas Tuchel: “This is unbelievable. To share it with everybody is unbelievable. I don’t know what to feel. The players were determined to win this.”\r\nThiago Silva was on the losing side in last years final. This year, he finally got his hands on the winners medal (although he wasnt able to finish the game due to injury)\r\nChelsea lift the Champions League trophy for the first time since 2012.\r\nNo fairytale ending for Citys Aguero who has just played his last game for the team. City did win the Premier League and the League Cup. Just not club footballs biggest prize\r\nWinners of Champions League for the second time. One goal separated the two sides…. the one that mattered.\r\nCitys wait for that trophy continues… they become the second Manchester side to lose a European final this week.\r\nFinal five minutes of normal time. Will City take it to extra-time? Will Chelsea hold on (and add more)?\r\nCity pressing. Aguero chips, Mendy catches it well. Like a Curtly Ambrose bouncer behind the stumps.\r\n', '2021-05-29T211450Z_894872287_UP1EH5T1N0OMB_RTRMADP_3_SOCCER-CHAMPIONS-MCI-CHE-REPORT.jpg', 2, NULL, '2021-08-21 13:35:41'),
(49, '​ការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បង្ការ​ជំងឺ​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​ ​ដល់​យុវវ័យ​នៅ​កម្ពុជា​សម្រេច​បាន​ ​៤​២​.​៩​៥​% ​ក្នុងរយៈពេល​ ​២​០​ ​ថ្ងៃ​', 'ផ្តោត​ ​ប្តេជ្ញា​ចិត្ត​ ​ជំរុញ​។​ ​លក្ខណៈ​ទាំង​បី​នេះ​ពិពណ៌នា​យ៉ាងល្អ​បំផុត​អំពី​យុទ្ធនាការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​របស់​ប្រទេស​កម្ពុជា​ ​ចាប់តាំង​ពី​បាន​ចាប់ផ្តើម​លើកដំបូង​នៅ​ថ្ងៃ​ទី​ ​១​០​ ​ខែកុម្ភៈ​ឆ្នាំ​ ​២​០​២​១​ ​និង​បាន​ទទួលជោគ', 'ផ្តោត​ ​ប្តេជ្ញា​ចិត្ត​ ​ជំរុញ​។​ ​លក្ខណៈ​ទាំង​បី​នេះ​ពិពណ៌នា​យ៉ាងល្អ​បំផុត​អំពី​យុទ្ធនាការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​របស់​ប្រទេស​កម្ពុជា​ ​ចាប់តាំង​ពី​បាន​ចាប់ផ្តើម​លើកដំបូង​នៅ​ថ្ងៃ​ទី​ ​១​០​ ​ខែកុម្ភៈ​ឆ្នាំ​ ​២​០​២​១​ ​និង​បាន​ទទួលជោគជ័យ​យ៉ាង​ខ្លាំង​នៅ​ថ្ងៃ​ទី​ ​១​ ​ខែ​ឧសភា​ ​នៅ​ពេល​កងកម្លាំង​ប្រដាប់​អាវុធ​ត្រូវ​បាន​ដាក់​ពង្រាយ​ដើម្បី​អនុវត្ត​ការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បង្ការ​រោគ​យ៉ាង​ច្រើន​នៅ​តំបន់​ក្រហម​បិទ​ខ្ទប់​នានា​នៅ​ខែ​ឧសភា​។​\r\nនៅ​ថ្ងៃ​ទី​ ​១​ ​ខែ​សីហា​ ​ទិសដៅ​ថ្មី​មួយ​បាន​ចាប់ផ្តើម​ជាមួយនឹង​ការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បង្ការ​ជំងឺ​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​ ​ដល់​ក្មេង​ជំទង់​ដែល​មាន​អាយុ​ចន្លោះ​ពី​ ​១​២​ ​ទៅ​ ​១​៧​ ​ឆ្នាំ​ ​ហើយ​គិត​មកដល់​ថ្ងៃ​ទី​ ​២​០​ ​ខែ​សីហា​ ​ក្នុងរយៈ​ ​២​០​ ​ថ្ងៃក្រោយ​ពី​ការ​ចាប់ផ្តើម​យុទ្ធនាការ​នេះ​ ​ប្រទេស​កម្ពុជា​ជិត​ស​ម្រ​ច​ការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ដូ​ស​ទី​១​ ​ប្រភេទ​ ​ស៊ី​ណូ​វ៉ា​ក់​បាន​ចំនួន​ ​៥​០​% ​ហើយ​។​\r\n​រហូតមកដល់​បច្ចុប្បន្ននេះ​ ​ចាប់តាំង​ពី​ថ្ងៃ​ទី​ ​១​ ​ខែ​សីហា​ ​កុមារ​ចំនួន​ ​៨​៤​៥​,​០​៤​២​ ​នាក់​បាន​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ ​ប្រភេទ​ស៊ី​ណូ​វ៉ា​ក់​ចំនួន​មួយ​ដូ​ស​ ​ហើយ​ក្នុងរយៈពេល​ប៉ុន្មាន​ថ្ងៃ​ទៀត​ ​យុទ្ធនាការ​ចាក់​ដូ​ស​ទី​ ​២​ ​នឹង​ចាប់ផ្តើម​ ​ខណៈ​ការប៉ុនប៉ង​ដើម្បី​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បង្ការ​ដល់​ក្មេង​ជំទង់​ដែល​មាន​លក្ខណៈ​គ្រប់គ្រាន់​ជិត​ ​២​ ​លាន​នាក់​ដំណើរការ​ ​និង​សម្រេច​បាន​ ​ប្រហែល​នៅ​ខែកញ្ញា​។​\r\n​ចំនួន​អ្នក​ដែល​បាន​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ស្ទើរតែ​ពាក់កណ្តាល​ ​គឺ​៤​២​២​,​២​៨​៨​ ​ជា​ស្ត្រី​ ​មានតែ​ ​៣​០​២​ ​នាក់​ប៉ុណ្ណោះ​ត្រូវ​បាន​បដិសេធ​មិន​ឱ្យ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ ​ដោយសារ​លក្ខខណ្ឌ​សុខភាព​ផ្សេងៗ​។​\r\n\r\n​កម្ពុជា​គឺជា​ប្រទេស​មួយ​ក្នុងចំណោម​ប្រទេស​តិចតួច​នៅ​លើ​ពិភពលោក​ដែល​បាន​ចាប់ផ្តើម​ជំរុញ​ការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បង្ការ​ដល់​ក្មេង​ជំទង់​ដែល​មាន​អាយុ​ពី​ ​១​២​ ​ទៅ​ ​១​៧​ ​ឆ្នាំ​ ​យ៉ាងខ្លាំងក្លា​ ​ដោយសារ​ប្រទេស​នេះ​មានបំណង​បើក​សាលារៀន​ឡើងវិញ​នៅ​ខែ​តុលា​ ​ក្រោម​ការ​អនុវត្ត​ធម្មតា​បែបថ្មី​ ​និង​ប្រហែល​ជាលើកដំបូង​ក្នុងរយៈពេល​មួយ​ឆ្នាំ​ ​ដែល​អនុញ្ញាត​ឱ្យ​សិស្សានុសិស្ស​អាច​ត្រឡប់មក​ទទួលការ​បង្រៀន​ ​និង​រៀន​ដោយ​ផ្ទាល់​វិញ​ ​បន្ទាប់ពី​រៀន​ពី​ចម្ងាយ​តាម​អ៊ី​ន​ធឺ​ណេ​ត​អស់​រយៈពេល​ជាច្រើន​ខែ​។​\r\nការ​អនុវត្ត​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ដល់​ក្មេង​ជំទង់​ ​និង​រៀបចំ​ពួកគេ​ឱ្យ​ទទួល​បាន​ភាព​ស៊ាំ​សហគមន៍​ដើម្បី​អាច​ទៅ​សាលារៀន​បាន​ ​គឺជា​ការ​សម្រេច​ចិត្ត​របស់​នាយក​រដ្ឋ​ម​ន្រ្តី ​នៅ​ពេល​ដំណើរការ​នេះ​បាន​ ​និង​កំពុង​អនុវត្ត​ ​ខណៈ​ប្រទេស​អភិវឌ្ឍន៍​ជាច្រើន​នៅ​កំពុងតែ​ពិចារណា​សម្រេច​ចិត្ត​នៅឡើយ​។​\r\n\r\n​ការ​ជំរុញ​ឱ្យ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ដល់​កុមារ​អាយុ​ចន្លោះ​ពី​ ​១​២​ ​ទៅ​ ​១​៧​ ​ឆ្នាំ​ ​បាន​ចាប់ផ្តើម​អនុវត្ត​ស្ទើរតែ​គ្រប់​ខេត្ត​ហើយ​ ​ហេតុនេះ​ ​សុទិដ្ឋិនិយម​លើ​គោលដៅ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ឱ្យ​បាន​ប្រមាណ​ចំនួន​ ​២​ ​លាន​នាក់​ ​នៅ​ចុង​ខែកញ្ញា​ ​គឺជា​ការកំណត់​ពេល​ចុងក្រោយបំផុត​។​\r\n\r\n​ក្រៅ​ពីក្មេង​ជំទង់​អាយុ​ពី​ ​១​២​ ​ទៅ​ ​១​៧​ ​ឆ្នាំ​ ​រដ្ឋាភិបាល​ក៏​កំពុង​ពិចារណា​លើ​ការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​កុមារ​អាយុ​ ​១​០​ ​និង​ ​១​១​ ​ឆ្នាំ​ផង​ដែរ​ ​នៅ​ពេល​ទិន្នន័យ​វិទ្យាសាស្ត្រ​ ​និង​វេជ្ជសាស្ត្រ​ផ្តល់​គ្រប់គ្រាន់​បញ្ជាក់​ពី​ការ​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ទាំងនេះ​។​\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បង្ការ​ជំងឺ​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​ ​មាន​ប្រសិទ្ធ​ភាព​ដូចគ្នា​ទៅ​នឹង​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ដទៃទៀត​ដែល​កូន​របស់​អ្នក​បាន​ចាក់​ដែរ​។​ ​មេរោគ​ ​ដូចជា​ S​AR​S-​Co​V​-2 ​ដែល​ជា​មេរោគ​បង្ក​ឱ្យ​មាន​ជំងឺ​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​ ​ចូល​មក​លុកលុយ​ក្នុង​ខ្លួនប្រាណ​។​ ​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បញ្ឈប់​សកម្មភាព​ទាំងនេះ​ដោយ​បង្រៀន​ប្រព័ន្ធ​ការពារ​រាងកាយ​ឱ្យ​ស្គាល់​ ​និង​បង្កើត​អង្គ​បដិ​ប្រាណ​ដើម្បី​ប្រយុទ្ធ​ប្រឆាំង​នឹង​មេរោគ​។​ ​បន្ទាប់ពី​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​រួច​ ​កូន​របស់​អ្នកមាន​ឱកាស​ឆ្លង​ជំងឺ​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​ ​តិចតួច​។​ ​ប្រសិនបើ​ពួកគេ​ឆ្លង​វី​រុ​ស​ ​ពួកគេ​ប្រហែលជា​មិន​ឈឺ​ដូច​ក្មេង​ដែល​មិនបាន​ចាក់​វ៉ាក់សាំង​ទេ​។​\r\n\r\n​ការស្រាវជ្រាវ​បង្ហាញ​ថា​ ​វ៉ាក់សាំង​បង្ការ​ជំងឺ​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​ ​ទាំងអស់​ ​មាន​ប្រសិទ្ធ​ភាព​ខ្ពស់​ក្នុង​ការបញ្ឈប់​មនុស្ស​ពី​ការ​ឆ្លង​ជំងឺ​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​។​ ​វ៉ាក់សាំង​នេះ​ក៏​ជួយការ​ពារ​ជំងឺ​ធ្ងន់ធ្ងរ​ ​ការ​ចូល​មន្ទីរពេទ្យ​ ​និង​ការ​ស្លាប់​ចំពោះ​អ្នក​ដែល​ឆ្លង​កូ​វី​ដ​-​១​៩​ផង​ដែរ​។​', 'vaccine-to-femel.jpg', 4, NULL, '2021-08-21 13:43:49'),
(50, 'Britains legal cannabis market blossoms on Covid-19 demand', 'AFP – Britains legal cannabis market has boomed during the Coronavirus pandemic to become the second biggest after the United States, as consumers rushed to alleviate Covid-linked symptoms, industry experts say.', 'AFP – Britains legal cannabis market has boomed during the Coronavirus pandemic to become the second biggest after the United States, as consumers rushed to alleviate Covid-linked symptoms, industry experts say.\r\nCannabidiol or CBD, which is most commonly sold as an oil at high street retailers, is one of the active ingredients of non-psychoactive cannabis.\r\nCBD is touted as have relaxing and anti-inflammatory properties, but experts argue the market has long suffered from questions about its efficacy and a lack of regulation.\r\nBritains Food Standards Agency now regulates the sector and its marketing, after the European Union classified CBD as food in 2019.\r\nSuch products will generate sales of £690 million in 2021, according to the Association for the Cannabinoid Industry (ACI).\r\nThat was almost a third higher than the UK trade group’s pre-pandemic 2019 projection.\r\n“The pandemic increased CBD demand because there obviously were stress, sleep problems, anxiety, these kind of risks,” ACI co-founder Steve Moore said.\r\nBritain has experienced a “quiet cannabis revolution” that has transformed it into “the world’s second-largest consumer cannabinoids market”, ACI said.\r\nSuch products are stripped of psychoactive tetrahydrocannabinol (THC molecules), which are found in recreational cannabis, which remains illegal in Britain.\r\nThe state-run National Health Service warns there is “no guarantee” that products claiming to be medical cannabis and sold in health stores as food supplements, such as CBD oil, are of “good quality or provide any health benefits”.\r\nThe UK allows the sale of hemp products that can be made only from the cannabis plant’s fibres or seeds, but not the buds.\r\nAside from Covid, such products have also experienced strong demand from Britons seeking to ease pain from chronic illnesses such as severe arthritis.\r\nBritish charity Versus Arthritis recommends patients contemplating CBD should consult their doctor beforehand. It also wants more work done to understand its impact.\r\nFaced with booming sales, Professor Sagnik Bhattacharyya, who researches psychotic and substance abuse disorders at King’s College London, says clinical trials are needed.\r\n“CBD products available over the counter from many shops or online may not contain what it says on the tin,” Bhattacharyya said, adding they can include potentially harmful substances.\r\n“Most importantly, there is no definitive evidence as yet that CBD would work for any of the myriad health conditions that it is supposed to benefit, except for certain types of epilepsy.”\r\nDespite those concerns, Joe Oliver, head of British-based cannabidiol firm LDN CBD, says his products help those with chronic illness.\r\n', '25471.jpg', 1, NULL, '2021-08-21 13:53:27'),
(51, 'ស្ទឹងត្រែងរកឃើញអ្នកឆ្លងវីរុសបំប្លែងខ្លួនថ្មីប្រភេទដែលតា (Delta) ៧នាក់', 'រដ្ឋបាលខេត្តស្ទឹងត្រែងបានប្រកាសពីការរកឃើញករណីឆ្លងវីរុសបំប្លែងខ្លួនថ្មីប្រភេទដែលតា (Delta) ចំនួន ៧នាក់ នៅថ្ងៃទី ១៧ ខែសីហានេះ ខណៈករណីឆ្លងនៅខេត្តនេះ នៅតែមានអត្រាទាប។', 'រដ្ឋបាលខេត្តស្ទឹងត្រែងបានប្រកាសពីការរកឃើញករណីឆ្លងវីរុសបំប្លែងខ្លួនថ្មីប្រភេទដែលតា (Delta) ចំនួន ៧នាក់ នៅថ្ងៃទី ១៧ ខែសីហានេះ ខណៈករណីឆ្លងនៅខេត្តនេះ នៅតែមានអត្រាទាប។\r\nមន្ទីរសុខាភិបាលខេត្ត ទើបទទួលបានលទ្ធផលរបស់សំណាកដែលបានបញ្ជូនទៅធ្វើតេស្តនៅវិទ្យាស្ថានប៉ាស្ទ័រ ក្នុងនោះ ៧សំណាក វិជ្ជមានវីរុសបំប្លែងខ្លួនថ្មីប្រភេទដែលតា (Delta)។ ទន្ទឹមនឹងនេះ មន្ទីរសុខាភិបាលខេត្តក៏បានបញ្ជូនសំណាក ទៅធ្វើតេស្តបន្ថែមទៀតនៅវិទ្យាស្ថានប៉ាស្ទ័រផងដែរ។ គិតត្រឹមថ្ងៃទី ១៦ ខែសីហា ខេត្តស្ទឹងត្រែងមានករណីឆ្លងសរុបចំនួន ៧០៨នាក់ និង ជាសះស្បើយចំនួន ៤៨៥នាក់៕\r\n\r\nរដ្ឋមន្ត្រីក្រសួងទេសចរណ៍កំពុងជួបពិភាក្សាជាមួយតំណាងឧស្សាហកម្មនៅថ្ងៃនេះ (ថ្ងៃសុក្រ) ។ នេះគឺជាកិច្ចប្រជុំដំបូងដែលរៀបចំឡើងដើម្បីត្រៀមទទួលភ្ញៀវទេសចរអន្តរជាតិ នៅពេលដែលមេរោគកូរ៉ូណាត្រូវបានគ្រប់គ្រង។\r\nកិច្ចពិភាក្សានេះក៏នឹងពិនិត្យមើលផងដែរថាតើធ្វើដូចម្តេចដើម្បីទទួលបានផលចំណេញពីកំណើនភ្ញៀវទេសចរក្នុងស្រុកដែលកំពុងចាប់ផ្តើមមានសកម្មភាពជុំវិញប្រទេសម្តងទៀត។ វាអាចមានហេតុផលសុទិដ្ឋិនិយមខ្លះ ចំពោះការវិលត្រឡប់មករកភាពប្រក្រតីវិញ។ កាលពីយប់មិញសាលារាជធានីភ្នំពេញបានប្រកាសថាខ្លួននឹងបញ្ចប់បម្រាមគោចរចាប់ពីម៉ោង ១០ យប់ដល់ម៉ោង ៣ ទៀបភ្លឺ ទោះបីជាការរឹតត្បិតផ្សេងទៀតនៅបន្តមានក៏ដោយ។\r\nក្រុមការងារនេះត្រូវបានបង្កើតឡើងកាលពីខែមុន។ តំណាងមកពីក្រសួងនឹងជួបជាមួយតំណាងវិស័យឯកជនចំនួន ៤៣ នាក់។ ពួកគេនឹងមានឱកាសផ្តល់ធាតុចូលលើផែនទីបង្ហាញផ្លូវរបស់រដ្ឋាភិបាលសម្រាប់ការងើបឡើងវិញនៃឧស្សាហកម្មទេសចរណ៍។ លោកនាយករដ្ឋមន្រ្តី ហ៊ុន សែន មានប្រសាសន៍ថា ប្រសិនបើផែនទីបង្ហាញផ្លូវត្រូវបានអនុវត្តតាម ប្រទេសអាចទទួលបានទេសចរអន្តរជាតិចំនួន ៧ លាននាក់ នៅត្រឹមឆ្នាំ ២០២៥ ។\r\nនៅឆ្នាំ ២០១៩ មានភ្ញៀវទេសចរបរទេសជាង ៦.៦ លាននាក់បានមកកម្ពុជាដែលបានរួមចំណែកជិត ២០% នៃផលិតផលក្នុងស្រុកសរុប។ ការមកដល់របស់ភ្ញៀវទេសចរកាលពីឆ្នាំមុនបានធ្លាក់ចុះដល់ ១.៣ លាននាក់ ដែលរួមចំណែកបានត្រឹមតែ ៣% នៃទំហំសេដ្ឋកិច្ចប៉ុណ្ណោះ។\r\nលោក Arnaud Darc ប្រធានសមាគមភោជនីយដ្ឋានកម្ពុជា បានមានប្រសាសន៍ថា “យើងមិនអាចរង់ចាំជំងឺរាតត្បាតនេះចប់ទេ ដោយសារមេរោគនេះទំនងជាមិនចេញពីយើងឡើយ យើងគ្មានជម្រើសក្រៅពីបន្តរស់នៅ ធ្វើការ និងរៀនសូត្រជាមួយវាទេ”៕\r\n', 'delta-sample.jpg', 4, NULL, '2021-08-21 14:01:01');
INSERT INTO `post` (`post_id`, `title`, `short`, `description`, `image`, `categoryid`, `user_id`, `date`) VALUES
(52, 'Domestication and history', 'corn, (Zea mays), also called Indian corn or maize, cereal plant of the grass family (Poaceae) and its edible grain. The domesticated crop originated in the Americas and is one of the most widely distributed of the world’s fo', 'Balsas teosinte (Zea mays parviglumis), a wild grass. Its culture had spread as far north as southern Maine by the time of European settlement of North America, and Native Americans taught European colonists to grow the indigenous grains. Since its introduction into Europe by Christopher Columbus and other explorers and colonizers, corn has spread to all areas of the world suitable to its cultivation. It is grown from 58° N latitude in Canada and Russia to 40° S latitude in South America, with a corn crop maturing somewhere in the world nearly every month of the year. It is the most important crop in the United States and is a staple food in many places.The corn plant is a tall annual grass with a stout, erect, solid stem. The large narrow leaves have wavy margins and are spaced alternately on opposite sides of the stem. Staminate (male) flowers are borne on the tassel terminating the main axis of the stem. The pistillate (female) inflorescences, which mature to become the edible ears, are spikes with a thickened axis, bearing paired spikelets in longitudinal rows; each row of paired spikelets normally produces two rows of grain. Varieties of yellow and white corn are the most popular as food, though there are varieties with red, blue, pink, and black kernels, often banded, spotted, or striped. Each ear is enclosed by modified leaves called shucks or husks.Commercial classifications, based mainly on kernel texture, include dent corn, flint corn, flour corn, sweet corn, and popcorn. Dent corn, primarily grown as animal feed and for food manufacturing, is characterized by a depression in the crown of the kernel caused by unequal drying of the hard and soft starch making up the kernel. Flint corn, containing little soft starch, has no depression; it is used for decoration and is eaten as hominy in the Americas. Flour corn, composed largely of soft starch, has soft, mealy, easily ground kernels and is an important source of corn flour. Sweet corn, commonly sold fresh, frozen, or canned as a vegetable, has wrinkled translucent seeds; the plant sugar is not converted to starch as in othertypes. Popcorn, an extreme type of flint corn characterized by small hard kernels, is devoid of soft starch, and heating causes the moisture in the cells to expand, making the kernels explode. Improvements in corn have resulted from hybridization, based on crossbreeding of superior inbred strains.', 'Ears-corn.jpg', 3, NULL, '2021-08-21 14:53:16'),
(53, 'Biofuel', 'Corn is also used to produce ethanol (ethyl alcohol), a first-generation liquid biofuel. In the United States corn ethanol is typically blended with gasoline to produce “gasohol,” an automotive fuel that is 10 percent ethanol', 'Corn is also used to produce ethanol (ethyl alcohol), a first-generation liquid biofuel. In the United States corn ethanol is typically blended with gasoline to produce “gasohol,” an automotive fuel that is 10 percent ethanol. Although corn-based biofuels were initially touted as environmentally friendly alternatives to petroleum, their production diverts arable land and feedstock from the human food chain, sparking a “food versus fuel” debate. In addition, crops grown for biofuel can compete for the world’s natural habitats, and the emphasis on ethanol derived from corn has shifted grasslands and brushlands to corn monocultures in some places, impacting In addition, crops grown for biofuel can compete for the worlds natural habitats, and the emphasis on ethanol derived from corn has shifted grasslands and brushlands to corn monocultures in some places, impacting biodiversity. Beyond land-use changes, the process of growing corn to produce ethanol consumes fossil fuels in farming equipment, in fertilizer manufacturing, in corn transportation, and in ethanol distillation. In this respect, ethanol made from corn represents a relatively small energy gain; the energy gain from sugarcane is greater and that from cellulosic ethanol (made from nonedible plant parts such as agricultural waste) or algae biodiesel could be even greater, though the conversion technology is generally less efficient than that of first-generation biofuels\r\nCorn is also fermented into a number of alcoholic beverages, notably bourbon and other corn whiskeys.', 'Squares-polenta.jpg', 3, NULL, '2021-08-21 15:00:54');

